  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I am planning a 4 day Holiday in North India. Where can I go?",
  "response": "North India offers a variety of destinations that cater to different interests, whether you're looking for cultural experiences, natural beauty, or adventure. Here are a few suggestions for a 4-day trip:\n\n1. **Delhi and Agra**:\n   - **Day 1-2**: Explore Delhi, the capital city, known for its rich history and vibrant culture. Visit the Red Fort, Qutub Minar, Humayun's Tomb, India Gate, and Lotus Temple. Enjoy Delhi's street food and vibrant markets.\n   - **Day 3-4**: Travel to Agra to see the iconic Taj Mahal. You can also explore Agra Fort and, if time permits, visit Fatehpur Sikri, an ancient city nearby.\n\n2. **Rishikesh and Haridwar**:\n   - **Day 1-2**: Head to Rishikesh, known as the 'Yoga Capital of the World'. Enjoy the serene atmosphere by the Ganges, visit the Beatles Ashram, and, if you're up for adventure, try white-water rafting.\n   - **Day 3-4**: Visit Haridwar, one of the holiest cities in India. Witness the Ganga Aarti at Har Ki Pauri, explore local temples, and enjoy the spiritual ambiance.\n\n3. **Jaipur and Pushkar**:\n   - **Day 1-2**: Explore Jaipur, the Pink City. Visit Amber Fort, City Palace, Hawa Mahal, and Jantar Mantar. Enjoy shopping in local bazaars and trying Rajasthani cuisine.\n   - **Day 3-4**: Travel to Pushkar, a quaint town famous for its Brahma Temple and Camel Fair (if timed with your visit). Enjoy the serene Pushkar Lake and the unique charm of this town.\n\n4. **Shimla and Kufri**:\n   - **Day 1-2**: Spend time in Shimla, a popular hill station. Enjoy the mall road, visit the Ridge, Jakhoo Temple, and Kufri for panoramic views and some winter activities if you're visiting in the colder months.\n   - **Day 3-4**: Explore the local area further, relax and enjoy the cool climate and scenic beauty of the hills.\n\n5. **Chandigarh and Amritsar**:\n   - **Day 1-2**: Start with Chandigarh, known for its urban design and architecture. Visit the Rock Garden, Sukhna Lake, and Rose Garden.\n   - **Day 3-4**: Move to Amritsar, home of the Golden Temple. Don't miss the moving Wagah Border ceremony and Jallianwala Bagh memorial.\n\n6. **Manali**:\n   - **Day 1-4**: Spend all four days in Manali, a picturesque town in the Himalayas. Visit the Solang Valley, Rohtang Pass (season permitting), Hidimba Devi Temple, and enjoy nature walks or adventure sports.\n\nWhen planning your trip, consider travel time between destinations to maximize your 4 days. Also, check the weather and local events as they can greatly influence your travel experiences in North India.",
